com.pb.sawdust.util.collections

Class LinkedSetList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<E>
        • com.pb.sawdust.util.collections.AbstractSetList<E>
          • com.pb.sawdust.util.collections.LinkedSetList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the elements held by this collection.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    SetDeque<E>, SetList<E>, SetQueue<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Deque<E>, java.util.List<E>, java.util.Queue<E>, java.util.Set<E>

    public class LinkedSetList<E>
extends AbstractSetList<E>
implements SetDeque<E>
    The LinkedSetList is a AbstractSetList which uses an java.util.LinkedList as its backing list. As such, the list will be optimized for sequential, as opposed to random, access. As it is backed by a linked list, it also implements the SetDeque interface.
    See Also:
    ArraySetList

      • LinkedSetList

        public LinkedSetList(java.util.Collection<? extends E> c)
        Constructor which will create a new setlist containing all of the elements in a specified collection. The setlist will be initialized to the size of the collection. The ordering of the elements in the setlist will be the same as the iteration order of the elements in the collection, whether or not the iteration order is well-defined. If a given object exists more than once in the collection, an exception will be thrown, as this violates the set property of the setlist.
        Parameters:
        c - The collection holding the elements which the setlist will be initialized with.

      • LinkedSetList

        @SafeVarargs
public LinkedSetList(E... elements)
        Constructor which will create a new setlist containing all of the elements in a specified array. The setlist will be initialized to the size of the array. The ordering of the elements in the setlist will be the same as the array. If a given object exists more than once in the collection, an exception will be thrown, as this violates the set property of the setlist.
        Parameters:
        elements - The elements which the setlist will be initialized with.

    • Method Detail

      • getBackingList

        protected java.util.List<E> getBackingList(int initialSize)
        Description copied from class: AbstractSetList
        Get the list that will be used to hold the elements in this setlist and ensure list properties. This list should be empty and a reference to it should be unavailable to it outside of this method's scope. As this class generally calls this backing list for all of the methods specified in the List interface, the specific advantages and disadvantages of the list returned by this method are inherited by this instance.

        This method is used in the constructor, and should not be used elsewhere. This method should return a new empty instance of the backing list type, not a reference to the list used in this instance. That is, if this method is called repeatedly, a new object should be return, not a reference to one which has already been created. This requirement is to ensure data encapsulation in the SetList implementation.

        Specified by:
        getBackingList in class AbstractSetList<E>
        Parameters:
        initialSize - The size to initialize the list with. If a value less than 0 is entered, then a list with the default size should be returned.
        Returns:
        an empty list.
